issues.description: The Virtual Connect domain has a status of warning or minor.
issues.recommendation: Review the status and resolve the issue causing the domain error status if necessary.

issues.description: The boot mode in profile "Profile_2" is configured as Auto and some PXE, FC, and FCoE connections are not configured to boot BIOS.
issues.recommendation: Configure all PXE, FC, and FCoE connections to boot from BIOS, or change the boot mode to something other than Auto.

issues.description: Profile "Profile_2" has one or more connections configured with Use-BIOS boot settings. OneView does not support profile connections configured with a mixture of Use-BIOS and other boot settings.
issues.recommendation: The Virtual Connect Use-BIOS boot setting will be automatically changed to not bootable in OneView.

issues.description: Profile "Profile_2" FCoE connection 1 is configured for factory MAC and a factory WWN of 10:00:6C:C2:17:39:95:A1. The WWN for this connection may change after migration to OneView.
issues.recommendation: After the migration task has completed, validate the WWNs of the migrated profiles for any potential changes. If a WWN change occurred, change the SAN fabric and storage configuration to reflect the new WWNs before powering on the servers.

issues.description: Profile "Profile_2" FCoE connection 2 is configured for factory MAC and a factory WWN of 10:00:6C:C2:17:39:95:A9. The WWN for this connection may change after migration to OneView.

issues.description: Profile "Profile_9" is configured for UEFI boot and is assigned to a server that does not support UEFI.
issues.recommendation: Remove the UEFI boot settings from the profile.
